The cancer is
an occupying force.

144
00:08:54,389 --> 00:08:57,323
I want to surrender.

145
00:08:57,325 --> 00:09:00,943
While I still have my dignity.

146
00:09:03,814 --> 00:09:07,733
- You are considering ending your life?
- Suicide seems

147
00:09:07,735 --> 00:09:11,204
like a valid solution
to my problem.

148
00:09:13,173 --> 00:09:15,858
How does that make you feel?

149
00:09:20,163 --> 00:09:22,431
Alive.

150
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:28,337
How does it make you feel?

151
00:09:30,807 --> 00:09:34,293
I've always found the idea
of death comforting.

152
00:09:34,295 --> 00:09:37,563
The thought that my life
could end at any moment

153
00:09:37,565 --> 00:09:40,566
frees me to fully appreciate

154
00:09:40,568 --> 00:09:42,868
the beauty, and art,

155
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:44,870
and horror

156
00:09:44,872 --> 00:09:46,939
of everything
this world has to offer.

157
00:09:46,941 --> 00:09:49,675
A death benefit?

158
00:09:49,677 --> 00:09:52,061
Upon taking his
own life, Socrates

159
00:09:52,063 --> 00:09:55,214
offered a rooster to the god
of healing, Asclepius,

160
00:09:55,216 --> 00:09:57,233
to pay his debt.

161
00:09:57,235 --> 00:10:00,419
What debt might that be?

162
00:10:00,421 --> 00:10:02,788
To Socrates, death
was not a defeat...

163
00:10:05,058 --> 00:10:07,093
...but a cure.

164
00:10:14,985 --> 00:10:18,321
Gentlemen...

165
00:10:18,323 --> 00:10:21,157
Local police were supposed
to exterminate the bees

166
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:23,960
so we could work the crime scene.
Apparently, someone shut that down.

167
00:10:23,962 --> 00:10:26,829
- I did. - He did.
- Jimmy?

168
00:10:26,831 --> 00:10:29,081
Well, I love bees.

169
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:31,584
Did you know that the drone

170
00:10:31,586 --> 00:10:34,453
is nature's most talented
suicidal swordsman?

171
00:10:34,455 --> 00:10:36,455
When the drone
mates with the queen,

172
00:10:36,457 --> 00:10:38,791
his ejaculation
is so explosive,

173
00:10:38,793 --> 00:10:40,793
it's audible to the human ear.

174
00:10:40,795 --> 00:10:42,678
All right.

175
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,714
How long has he been out here?

176
00:10:44,716 --> 00:10:47,713
Ah, from de-comp, I'd estimate two weeks.

177
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,019
Which makes sense with how
much honey is being produced.

178
00:10:51,972 --> 00:10:54,857
Do bees naturally hive
in human carcasses like this?

179
00:10:54,859 --> 00:10:58,778
No. The victim was purposely
repurposed as a human apiary.

180
00:10:58,780 --> 00:11:00,780
Purposely.

181
00:11:00,782 --> 00:11:03,733
Somebody removed
the eyes and part

182
00:11:03,735 --> 00:11:06,402
of the brain to
make room for the hive.

183
00:11:08,372 --> 00:11:14,377
Zeller's out in the field, otherwise
I'd ask him to help me with this.

184
00:11:14,379 --> 00:11:17,363
I was a surgeon and
a doctor, yes. Have you found

185
00:11:17,365 --> 00:11:19,615
any evidence on
the Muralist's friend?

186
00:11:19,617 --> 00:11:22,918
That's what I need your help with.
Might not have been a friend.

187
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,920
Might not have even
been an acquaintance.

188
00:11:24,922 --> 00:11:26,989
Whoever killed him,
understood him.

189
00:11:26,991 --> 00:11:29,241
So often you open your mouth

190
00:11:29,243 --> 00:11:32,144
and I hear Will Graham's
words come out.

191
00:11:32,146 --> 00:11:35,564
I have an arrangement
with Will.

192
00:11:35,566 --> 00:11:38,517
He's agreed to consult
with me on cases,

193
00:11:38,519 --> 00:11:41,003
if I keep investigating
the murders he's accused of.

194
00:11:41,005 --> 00:11:44,390
I'm happy to hear that.

195
00:11:44,392 --> 00:11:47,493
Will needs a champion
now more than ever.

196
00:11:47,495 --> 00:11:50,379
He has you, doesn't he?

197
00:11:50,381 --> 00:11:53,449
You think there's a chance he
could be innocent. I know you do.

198
00:11:55,402 --> 00:11:57,503
I believe there is
a possibility.

199
00:11:57,505 --> 00:12:00,840
I'm just relieved he's not saying
the killer is you anymore.

200
00:12:00,842 --> 00:12:04,293
At least not to me.

201
00:12:06,063 --> 00:12:08,130
Who does Will believe
killed the Muralist?

202
00:12:08,132 --> 00:12:10,116
Doesn't know.

203
00:12:10,118 --> 00:12:12,435
He thinks if
James Gray's killer

204
00:12:12,437 --> 00:12:14,437
hid him in the mural, he may
have hid something else.

205
00:12:14,439 --> 00:12:17,857
A signature?

206
00:12:17,859 --> 00:12:20,092
What kind of killer

207
00:12:20,094 --> 00:12:23,729
seeks to depict the unconscious,
instinctual striving of his victim

208
00:12:23,731 --> 00:12:26,982
by sewing him into
a human mural?

209
00:12:26,984 --> 00:12:30,252
It wasn't just for appearances.

210
00:12:30,254 --> 00:12:34,123
You have to get to the truth
beneath the appearances.

211
00:12:34,125 --> 00:12:38,043
Only by going deep beneath
the skin will you understand

212
00:12:38,045 --> 00:12:40,796
the nature of this
killer's pathology.

213
00:12:46,887 --> 00:12:49,872
Before I start
asking you questions,

214
00:12:49,874 --> 00:12:52,842
I need some confidence that
you will be telling the truth

215
00:12:52,844 --> 00:12:55,878
- when you answer.
- What's this?

216
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:58,314
A consent form.
You're agreeing

217
00:12:58,316 --> 00:13:01,350
to a narcoanalytic
interview. You. Me.

218
00:13:01,352 --> 00:13:03,903
And our old friend,
sodium amytal.

219
00:13:03,905 --> 00:13:06,021
A little something
to loosen my tongue?

220
00:13:06,023 --> 00:13:08,357
Something lawfully
used in the evaluation

221
00:13:08,359 --> 00:13:10,159
of psychotic patients.

222
00:13:10,161 --> 00:13:12,194
What would you use

223
00:13:12,196 --> 00:13:15,114
to induce memory loss in a
patient, psychotic or otherwise?

224
00:13:15,116 --> 00:13:18,984
The protein synthesis
that moves memories

225
00:13:18,986 --> 00:13:22,755
from short-term to long-term
can be interrupted,

226
00:13:22,757 --> 00:13:26,208
but that requires
tools and skills.

227
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:28,961
And a certain level
of unorthodoxy.

228
00:13:28,963 --> 00:13:32,047
Does Hannibal Lecter possess
those tools and skills?

229
00:13:32,049 --> 00:13:35,468
Dr. Lecter has indicated
to me that he is open

230
00:13:35,470 --> 00:13:38,521
to the unorthodox when
it comes to treating patients.

231
00:13:38,523 --> 00:13:40,523
I wonder how that
subject came up...

232
00:13:40,525 --> 00:13:43,642
Sharing stories
of the unorthodox.

233
00:13:43,644 --> 00:13:47,480
Sign here.

234
00:14:50,710 --> 00:14:53,429
I want you to draw
a clock for me.

235
00:14:57,884 --> 00:15:01,053
(muffled): Did Dr. Lecter
administer any drug therapies

236
00:15:01,055 --> 00:15:03,072
during your sessions together?

237
00:15:03,074 --> 00:15:05,391
Sedatives...

238
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:15,968
The strobe causes neurons
to fire en masse,

239
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:18,988
like striking many
piano keys at once.

240
00:15:22,993 --> 00:15:25,244
<i>The strobe causes neurons</i>
<i>to fire en masse,</i>

241
00:15:25,246 --> 00:15:27,830
<i>like striking many...</i>

242
00:15:29,799 --> 00:15:33,369
The dissonance might foster
a change in your mind.

243
00:15:38,308 --> 00:15:40,009
Is something wrong?

244
00:15:45,015 --> 00:15:47,616
Will...?

245
00:15:51,154 --> 00:15:53,856
He was inducing seizures.

246
00:15:53,858 --> 00:15:56,442
He was encouraging them.
The blackouts.

247
00:15:56,444 --> 00:15:58,611
The lost time.

248
00:15:58,613 --> 00:16:02,064
It was strategic.
It was planned.

249
00:16:04,217 --> 00:16:06,485
You would only see a seizure
response in a brain

250
00:16:06,487 --> 00:16:08,921
afflicted with
photosensitive epilepsy.

251
00:16:08,923 --> 00:16:11,757
Or afflicted by something
just as damaging.

252
00:16:11,759 --> 00:16:13,809
Like encephalitis.

253
00:16:19,349 --> 00:16:23,302
That would suggest a radically
unorthodox form of therapy.

254
00:16:23,304 --> 00:16:25,162
Yes, it would.

